memorize all this?

00:06.979 --> 00:08.212
Let's just go over it again.

00:08.213 --> 00:10.280
Kingdom, phylum, class...

00:10.281 --> 00:13.751
Order, family, genus, species.

00:13.752 --> 00:15.853
I use a mnemonic device.

00:15.854 --> 00:19.690
"Kevin, please come
over for gay sex."

00:19.691 --> 00:22.192
Why wouldn't you use "Karen"?

00:22.193 --> 00:23.761
'Cause it's gay sex, dummy.

00:23.762 --> 00:25.328
So use "great".

00:25.329 --> 00:27.296
Now I can't remember anything.
Thanks!

00:27.297 --> 00:29.265
God, why do we always wind up
in this position?

00:29.266 --> 00:30.900
For all the time you spend here,
you'd think we wouldn't

00:30.901 --> 00:32.201
have to cram so much.

00:32.202 --> 00:33.602
Maybe we never get any work
done because we have

00:33.603 --> 00:35.085
so much fun hanging out
together.

00:35.086 --> 00:38.022
Definitely, maybe that's why.

00:38.877 --> 00:44.212
Ah, the duali-Dean of man.

00:44.213 --> 00:46.848
I'm dressed this way because I
have good news and bad news.

00:46.849 --> 00:48.850
You have got to be kidding me.

00:48.851 --> 00:51.820
The bad news is Professor Kane
has the flu.

00:51.821 --> 00:54.322
The good news is biology class
is canceled...

00:56.192 --> 00:57.258
After you.

00:57.259 --> 01:00.027
What a gentleman.

01:00.028 --> 01:02.697
Guys, we don't have to cram
last minute anymore.

01:02.698 --> 01:04.732
Last minute got
moved to tomorrow.

01:04.733 --> 01:06.734
Three-hour lunch? Three-hour
lunch? Three-hour lunch?

01:06.735 --> 01:07.968
Three hours?

01:07.969 --> 01:09.704
I could watch the first half of
three movies.

01:09.705 --> 01:11.038
Ooh, I don't have to go
to the fast food

01:11.039 --> 01:12.173
restaurant across the street.

01:12.174 --> 01:13.574
I can go to the fancy one
across town.

01:13.575 --> 01:14.808
Their manager wears a tie.

01:14.809 --> 01:16.242
If we don't eat, we can
make-believe

01:16.243 --> 01:17.711
an whole episode's worth of
Inspector Spacetime

01:17.712 --> 01:19.112
- in the Dreamatorium.
- Word.

01:19.113 --> 01:20.947
Yeah.

01:20.948 --> 01:23.016
Maybe we should go
to Señor Kevin's.

01:23.017 --> 01:25.018
Britta, didn't you want to try
that new cage-free bean burrito?

01:25.019 --> 01:27.420
The tortillas are made with
micro-financed flour.

01:27.421 --> 01:28.955
Troy, you could drive.

01:28.956 --> 01:30.856
You always like that spiral
parking ramp.

01:30.857 --> 01:32.925
You just keep turning left,
but you end up up!

01:32.926 --> 01:35.060
I can't go to Señor Kevin's.
The manager and I are enemies.

01:35.061 --> 01:36.394
<i>He said Die Hard was bad.</i>

01:36.395 --> 01:37.763
