the Dreamatorium works.

01:46.705 --> 01:48.606
- Today's the perfect day for it.
- But I want to...

01:48.607 --> 01:50.208
Abed, don't you think today's

01:50.209 --> 01:51.743
- the perfect day for it?
- No.

01:51.744 --> 01:54.212
- Abed.
- Is this a social cue?

01:54.213 --> 01:58.420
<i>I left my Puttin' On the Ritz
cane in here earlier.</i>

01:59.384 --> 02:01.018
I know it probably
has another name,

02:01.019 --> 02:04.287
but, um, can I be perfectly
honest with you guys?

02:04.288 --> 02:06.189
I think I went too
far with this one.

02:06.190 --> 02:10.460
I have to go to the bank today.

02:10.461 --> 02:12.162
What am I supposed to tell
people in line?

02:12.163 --> 02:14.998
"I had good news and bad news"?

02:14.999 --> 02:16.967
Come on, Craig.

02:16.968 --> 02:19.235
Get you life together.

02:23.839 --> 02:27.409
♪ Give me some more,
time in a dream ♪

02:27.410 --> 02:30.846
