observation.

05:26.578 --> 05:28.246
I'm able to simulate
any of the study group

05:28.247 --> 05:31.448
and even a half-accurate Chang
in over 7,000 unique situations.

05:31.449 --> 05:35.018
Abed, it's cardboard tubes
and a funnel.

05:35.019 --> 05:36.286
Well you see it that way
because it's calibrated

05:36.287 --> 05:37.854
to a specific level
of brain function.

05:37.855 --> 05:40.057
Right. I'm stupid.

05:40.058 --> 05:42.359
Not stupid, just less able to
see what I see.

05:42.360 --> 05:45.429
Gee, you've got it
all figured out.

05:47.764 --> 05:50.532
King of toilet paper rolls
over here.

05:50.533 --> 05:54.303
Hey, Troy, I'm glad you called.

05:54.304 --> 05:55.438
Your lunch is going well, right?

05:55.439 --> 05:57.173
Yeah, just checking on Abed.

05:57.174 --> 05:59.075
Making sure he's okay.

05:59.076 --> 06:01.510
What? He's fine.

06:01.511 --> 06:03.411
He just implied I operate
on a lower level

06:03.412 --> 06:06.147
of brain function,
so business as usual.

06:06.148 --> 06:09.650
Great, um, just, you know,
make sure he stays comfortable.

06:09.651 --> 06:11.252
