of everything, Annie.

13:08.849 --> 13:11.484
With Abed gone
and Troy and Britta together,

13:11.485 --> 13:13.386
there's nothing standing
in the way of us.

13:13.387 --> 13:14.587
Wait, what?

13:14.588 --> 13:15.855
Come on.

13:15.856 --> 13:16.923
This is you dream.

13:16.924 --> 13:19.858
This is why you
played matchmaker.

13:19.859 --> 13:22.494
This is what's important to you.

13:22.495 --> 13:24.963
You are not Jeff.

13:24.964 --> 13:27.966
Because Jeff cares about Abed.

13:27.967 --> 13:29.601
And I did not push
Troy and Britta together

13:29.602 --> 13:30.869
so this would happen.

13:30.870 --> 13:32.538
I did it because I thought
they were cute together

13:32.539 --> 13:34.540
and this would
have been a bonus.

13:34.541 --> 13:36.441
And we are not here.

13:36.442 --> 13:39.843
And I'm not staying here because
I hate whoever you are.

13:39.844 --> 13:41.845
You should probably
storm off in...

13:41.846 --> 13:43.247
Oh!

13:43.248 --> 13:45.183
In place.

13:54.243 --> 13:55.410
Where do you wanna go next?

13:55.411 --> 13:57.712
I wanna be alone.

13:57.713 --> 13:59.547
Sounds good to me.

13:59.548 --> 14:02.483
Execute simulation,
Annie/Annie.

14:04.954 --> 14:06.854
There.

14:06.855 --> 14:08.222
Now we're alone.

14:08.223 --> 14:10.825
Great, so you're me now.

14:10.826 --> 14:13.227
Why are you blowing
our magic moment with Jeff?

14:13.228 --> 14:14.361
It's not magic.

14:14.362 --> 14:15.495
It's not even real.

14:15.496 --> 14:17.998
But we love Jeff.

14:17.999 --> 14:20.734
No, we don't.

14:20.735 --> 14:23.903
We're just in love
with the idea of being loved.

14:23.904 --> 14:25.872
And if we can teach a guy
like Jeff to do it,

14:25.873 --> 14:27.874
we'll never be unloved.

14:27.875 --> 14:30.576
So we keep running the same
scenario over and over

14:30.577 --> 14:32.078
hoping for a different result.

14:32.079 --> 14:33.779
Running scenarios.

14:33.780 --> 14:35.048
Careful now.

14:35.049 --> 14:38.317
You're starting
to sound like Abed.

14:38.318 --> 14:42.087
<i>So... I probably shouldn't say
things like "Star Wars.</i>

14:42.088 --> 14:44.589
<i>Zardoz, Cougar Town,
cool, cool, cool."</i>

14:44.590 --> 14:46.225
- Stop it.
- Pop culture, pop culture.

14:46.226 --> 14:49.228
- I'm on a TV show.
- You're gonna get in trouble.

14:49.229 --> 14:50.996
Meta, meta.

14:50.997 --> 14:52.197
It's Abed!

14:52.198 --> 14:53.765
I got an Abed here!

14:53.766 --> 14:54.999
Get him!

14:55.000 --> 14:56.000
That's it.

14:56.001 --> 14:57.601
I find you guilty of being Abed.

14:57.602 --> 14:59.036
You're under arrest!

14:59.037 --> 15:00.304
Can I just interject and say

15:00.305 --> 15:03.241
I don't know what
the hell's going on?

15:09.314 --> 15:12.082
This time you'll never get out.

15:12.083 --> 15:14.017
Abed?

15:16.754 --> 15:17.754
Abed.

15:17.755 --> 15:18.989
Yeah.

15:18.990 --> 15:20.623
I found you by turning into you,
how cool is that?

15:20.624 --> 15:22.225
Cool.
Cool, cool, cool.

15:22.226 --> 15:23.826
Tell me where we are
so I can pretend to see it.

15:23.827 --> 15:25.495
We're inside a locker.

15:25.496 --> 15:28.430
It's where I spent a lot of time
in junior high.

15:28.431 --> 15:29.965
You think this is
where we'd put you?

15:29.966 --> 15:32.734
- You know that's absurd, right?
- Well, I'm not stupid.

15:32.735 --> 15:34.904
You can see I've increased
the square footage.

15:34.905 --> 15:36.571
It's a metaphorical locker.

15:36.572 --> 15:37.839
It's a place where
people like me get put

15:37.840 --> 15:39.174
when everyone's finally
fed up with us.

15:39.175 --> 15:42.310
Abed, so maudlin.

15:42.311 --> 15:44.312
If you start turning
into a vampire...

15:44.313 --> 15:45.479
I've run the simulations,
Annie.

15:45.480 --> 15:46.814
I don't get married,
I don't invent

15:46.815 --> 15:48.316
a billion dollar website
that helps people have sex.

15:48.317 --> 15:50.551
I don't make in into Sundance,
Slamdance or Dance Pants.

15:50.552 --> 15:52.486
Troy invents Dance Pants
in 2019.

15:52.487 --> 15:53.988
Don't tell him, he needs to
stumble onto it.

15:53.989 --> 15:55.189
All right, listen.

15:55.190 --> 15:56.757
The scenarios you run in here

15:56.758 --> 16:00.160
are like...
great science fiction.

16:00.161 --> 16:03.797
They're impressive and detailed
and insightful,

16:03.798 --> 16:05.966
but they're not
accurate for crap.

16:05.967 --> 16:07.767
Science fiction never has been.

16:07.768 --> 16:09.269
<i>Look at 2001.</i>

16:09.270 --> 16:11.071
Did we have a space odyssey?

16:11.072 --> 16:13.407
No, we got snowboarding
in the Olympics

16:13.408 --> 16:15.041
and we over-validated
Carson Daily.

16:15.042 --> 16:17.410
- That poor guy.
- Yeah, cry me a river.

16:17.411 --> 16:18.978
My point is, your simulations

16:18.979 --> 16:20.879
are nothing more
than anxieties.

16:20.880 --> 16:22.348
You're afraid you don't fit in.

16:22.349 --> 16:23.950
You're afraid you'll be alone.

16:23.951 --> 16:26.819
Great news... you share
that with all of us,

16:26.820 --> 16:30.355
so you'll never be alone
and you'll always fit in.

16:30.356 --> 16:33.425
And, yes, that's why I meddled
with Troy and Britta.

16:33.426 --> 16:34.426
You caught me.

16:34.427 --> 16:35.860
I was trying to make life go

16:35.861 --> 16:37.228
according to some script.

16:37.229 --> 16:38.763
I can't.

16:38.764 --> 16:40.765
You can't.

16:40.766 --> 16:44.035
We both need to get more
comfortable winging it.

16:44.036 --> 16:45.503
At least it'll be less work.

16:45.504 --> 16:46.937
It would cut down my
Dreamatorium time

16:46.938 --> 16:48.339
by 18 hours a week.

16:48.340 --> 16:49.340
I could take up yoga.

16:49.341 --> 16:51.241
You've got the body type.

16:51.242 --> 16:53.077
Now let's get you out of here.

16:53.078 --> 16:54.311
I don't know how.

16:54.312 --> 16:56.046
These fake shackles
don't have a fake key.

16:56.047 --> 16:59.049
Isn't that what a...
quantum spanner's for?

16:59.050 --> 17:01.585
Technically, no.

17:01.586 --> 17:04.686
But that's fine.

17:09.326 --> 17:11.426
So should we get back to lunch?

17:11.428 --> 17:12.428
I guess so.

17:12.429 --> 17:13.429
A little more anticlimactic

17:13.430 --> 17:14.430
than I would have simulated it,

17:14.431 --> 17:17.233
- but whatever.
- Anticlimactic?

17:17.233 --> 17:19.201
Render environment
observo-deck,

17:19.202 --> 17:23.704
<i>H.M.S. Spacetime 12.</i>

17:23.705 --> 17:26.941
Inspector, set the tachyon drive
to hyperjump.

17:26.942 --> 17:28.943
We must get to the other side of
this star field

17:28.944 --> 17:31.679
before the Blorgons intercept.

17:31.680 --> 17:33.948
Blorgons in this sector?

17:33.949 --> 17:36.550
Well, this mission has gone
pear-shaped, indeed.

17:36.551 --> 17:38.719
Prepare to hyperjump
on my mark.

17:38.720 --> 17:41.088
Bugger the dovecoats,
inspector.

17:41.089 --> 17:42.890
We're too late! Blorgons!

17:42.891 --> 17:45.459
Eradicate! Eradicate!

17:45.460 --> 17:49.063
Our quantum blasters are
useless against their armor.

17:49.064 --> 17:51.431
We're as cooked as Lord Nelson's
mutton, we are.

17:51.432 --> 17:52.965
Not if I can help it.

17:52.966 --> 17:57.437
I'll see you on the other side
inspector... Wherever that is.

17:57.438 --> 18:00.806
Don't you mean
"whenever that is"?

18:04.145 --> 18:06.211
Take that, Blorgon scum!

18:06.212 --> 18:09.348
You'll blo-gon me
for this later.

18:09.349 --> 18:10.949
Ow, Annie!

18:10.950 --> 18:12.351
Oh, oh, my God!

18:12.352 --> 18:14.453
Abed, I'm so sorry.

18:14.454 --> 18:15.854
No, no, you're committing.

18:15.855 --> 18:17.022
This is good stuff.

18:17.023 --> 18:19.624
Thanks.

18:19.625 --> 18:21.760
I am Abed Nadir...

18:21.761 --> 18:23.928
And I don't know a lot of things
everyone else knows.

18:23.929 --> 18:25.963
I wander the universe
with my friend, Troy,

18:25.964 --> 18:27.465
doing whatever I want.

18:27.466 --> 18:30.868
Sometimes accidentally hurting
innocent unremarkables.

18:30.869 --> 18:34.305
This week, however, Troy went
to lunch and I adapted.

18:34.306 --> 18:37.375
I now have the ability
to enter the minds of others.

18:37.376 --> 18:39.576
- I'm hungry, are you hungry?
- Yeah.

18:39.577 --> 18:41.144
I'll make us buttered noodles.

18:41.145 --> 18:44.581
Using an elusive new
technique known as "empathy".

18:46.617 --> 18:48.718
So was the other fast food
place worth the drive, Shirley?

18:48.719 --> 18:50.620
You know, half way there I
thought, "What am I doing?

18:50.621 --> 18:52.655
It's the same fast food place
in a different location.

18:52.656 --> 18:55.124
Have the margins of my life
become so narrow?"

18:55.125 --> 18:56.825
So I went to the mall
and had pizza.

18:58.661 --> 19:01.530
Sounds like this has been a
game-changing day for all of us.

19:01.531 --> 19:03.299
I almost sat on my balls,

19:03.300 --> 19:06.802
but at the last second,
I made an adjustment.

19:06.803 --> 19:08.704
- Good job!
- Good work.

19:08.705 --> 19:10.138
Good job, man.

19:10.139 --> 19:11.372
Well, we had a good lunch, too.

19:11.373 --> 19:13.674
Yeah.

19:13.675 --> 19:15.243
<i>I spoke to the manager
about Die Hard,</i>

19:15.244 --> 19:16.811
and I told him he should be
ashamed of himself.

19:16.812 --> 19:18.179
Thanks.

19:18.180 --> 19:20.315
Sorry I bailed
on the Dreamatorium.

19:20.316 --> 19:24.319
It's okay, Annie did pretty
good in a pinch.

19:24.320 --> 19:27.787
All right, back to cramming?

19:27.788 --> 19:31.024
The people at the bank loved
my outfit.

19:31.025 --> 19:33.393
And they had all kinds of
questions about it

19:33.394 --> 19:34.894
and my answers seemed to amuse

19:34.895 --> 19:37.531
and... and even liberate
them a little.

19:37.532 --> 19:39.099
A few of us went to lunch

19:39.100 --> 19:43.068
and I had the deepest
conversation of my life.

19:43.069 --> 19:47.039
I gotta go,
I'm telling everybody.

19:47.040 --> 19:49.642
Hmm, maybe after
a long, dark night,

19:49.643 --> 19:51.244
the sun is starting
to rise on Greendale.

19:51.245 --> 19:54.247
Maybe. Maybe not.

19:54.248 --> 19:56.915
You never can tell what kind
of day you're gonna have.

19:56.916 --> 19:58.850
Okay, I didn't really avoid
sitting on them.

19:58.851 --> 20:00.685
I sat right on them.

20:00.686 --> 20:02.254
- Oh.
- Aw.

20:02.255 --> 20:03.555
- I'm sorry.
- Pierce, I'm sorry.

20:03.556 --> 20:04.856
Hurt like hell.

20:04.857 --> 20:06.791
I saw eagles.

20:17.442 --> 20:19.537
♪ Troy and Abed
in the morning ♪

20:19.538 --> 20:20.939
Today we're joined
by Annie Edison...

20:20.940 --> 20:22.206
- Hi!
- Who's gonna show us how

20:22.207 --> 20:23.641
to spruce up your
apartment on a budget.

20:23.642 --> 20:25.043
So, Annie, what
inspired this throw?

20:25.044 --> 20:27.478
Well, I just thought
that I'd cover up the stain

20:27.479 --> 20:29.646
where Abed spilled code red
on the couch last week.

20:29.647 --> 20:30.981
Oops. Crafty.

20:30.982 --> 20:32.583
And you have some tips
on entertaining.

20:32.584 --> 20:34.417
Yes, if you're
expecting company,

20:34.418 --> 20:36.720
but you don't have enough
chairs, you can bring out

20:36.721 --> 20:39.322
pillows from your bedroom and
use them on the floor

20:39.323 --> 20:40.757
for a Moroccan feel.

20:40.758 --> 20:42.859
- Ooh, a taste of the Orient.
- Ooh!

20:42.860 --> 20:45.527
Actually, boys, I have
a little surprise for you.

20:45.528 --> 20:46.562
- Uh-oh.
- While you two were out

20:46.563 --> 20:47.730
playing blazer tag...

20:47.731 --> 20:49.498
That's laser tag
with sport coats.

20:49.499 --> 20:53.102
I did a little extreme
bedroom makeover!

20:53.103 --> 20:56.438
I unbunked your beds and got
scrap fabric and...

20:56.439 --> 20:59.341
It's okay, buddy.

20:59.342 --> 21:00.341
We can put it back.

21:00.342 --> 21:01.542
We can put it back
the way it was.

21:01.543 --> 21:02.811
- I'm so sorry.
- It's okay.

21:02.812 --> 21:05.413
It's... cut, Garrett.

21:05.414 --> 21:06.715
Sorry!

